==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|grc|en}} {{term|φώνημα||tr=phōnēma||sound|lang=grc}}, from {{term|φωνέω||tr=phōneō||to sound|lang=grc}}, from {{term|φωνή||tr=phōnē||sound|lang=grc}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˈfəʊniːm/|lang=en}}
* {{a|US}} {{enPR|fōn'ēm}}, {{IPA|/ˈfoʊˌnim/|lang=en}}
* {{audio|En-us-phoneme.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}

* {{hyphenation|pho|neme|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# An indivisible [[unit]] of [[sound]] in a given language. A phoneme is an abstraction of the physical speech sounds ([[phone]]s) and may encompass several different phones.

